(44, 10, 11, 49, 3, 6, 6, 'a certain vessel descending unto him', 'Connection of Gentiles and Inclusion', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusion, as the ''vessel'' in Acts symbolizes the acceptance of Gentiles into the faith, paralleling Ephesians'' assertion that Gentiles are ''fellowheirs'' and partakers of God''s promise. Both passages emphasize the breaking down of barriers between Jews and Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 11, 43, 1, 51, 51, 'heaven opened', 'Connection of Heaven Opening', 'This connection highlights the theme of heaven being opened in both passages. In Acts 10:11, the vision of the vessel descending occurs as heaven opens, while John 1:51 speaks of seeing heaven open with angels ascending and descending.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 11, 45, 16, 25, 26, 'heaven opened', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation. In Acts 10:11, the vision represents God''s new message being revealed, while Romans 16:25-26 speaks of the mystery made manifest to all nations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 11, 1, 49, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation and guidance. In Acts, the vision of the vessel signifies God''s instruction to Peter, while Genesis speaks to the coming of Shiloh, a figure of authority and unity. Both passages emphasize a pivotal moment of divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 11, 23, 11, 6, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Unity and Gathering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of gathering and unity among diverse groups. Acts 10:11''s vision of a vessel descending suggests inclusivity, while Isaiah 11:12 speaks of gathering the dispersed from the four corners of the earth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
