(44, 10, 11, 26, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'Heaven Opened and Visions', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ''heavens were opened,'' suggesting a divine revelation. This connection highlights the significance of visions in both contexts, indicating a moment of spiritual insight.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 12, 1, 7, 8, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Beasts in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the categories of animals, specifically mentioning ''beasts'' and ''fowls.'' This connection highlights the significance of clean and unclean animals in God''s creation and commands.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 12, 23, 11, 6, 9, 'fourfooted beasts of the earth', 'Connection of Animals in Peace', 'This connection highlights the presence of various animals in both passages, emphasizing a vision of harmony among creatures. Acts 10:12 mentions ''fourfooted beasts'' while Isaiah 11:6-9 describes a peaceful coexistence of predators and prey.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 12, 23, 65, 25, 25, NULL, 'Animal Harmony in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of harmony among animals. Both passages depict a vision of peace where different creatures coexist without harm.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 12, 43, 7, 37, 37, NULL, 'Connection of Thirst and Creation', 'This connection highlights the theme of creation and sustenance. The ''fourfooted beasts'' in Acts suggest the diversity of life, while Jesus'' invitation to ''come unto me, and drink'' in John emphasizes spiritual nourishment.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 12, 46, 6, 9, 11, 'fourfooted beasts of the earth', 'Connection of Clean and Unclean', 'This connection highlights the distinction between clean and unclean, as seen in Acts with the mention of ''fourfooted beasts'' and the moral implications in 1 Corinthians regarding unrighteous behavior. Both passages emphasize the need for purification and transformation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 13, 43, 4, 31, 34, 'kill, and eat', 'Connection of Spiritual Nourishment', 'This connection highlights the theme of sustenance, where Peter is instructed to ''kill, and eat'' in a physical sense, while Jesus speaks of a different kind of ''meat'' that relates to fulfilling God''s will. Both passages emphasize the importance of spiritual nourishment over physical food.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 13, 24, 35, 2, 5, 'kill, and eat', 'Connection of Dietary Instructions', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine instruction regarding food and drink. In Acts, Peter is commanded to ''kill, and eat,'' while in Jeremiah, the Rechabites are offered wine to drink, showcasing contrasting responses to God''s directives.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
