(44, 10, 18, 44, 11, 11, 11, 'Simon, which was surnamed Peter', 'Connection of Peter''s Encounter', 'Both passages emphasize the arrival of men sent to Peter. The mention of ''three men'' in Acts 11:11 connects directly to the context of Peter being sought in Acts 10:18.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 10, 19, 44, 8, 29, 29, 'the Spirit said unto', 'Divine Guidance in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in directing the actions of the apostles. In each instance, the Spirit instructs Peter and Philip to engage with others, highlighting the theme of divine guidance in their missions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
